1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,170
My three disillusioned friends should have realized that top executives don't select major executives by drawing names from a hat.

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:19,250
I was talking about the seriousness of luck excusitis not long ago with a sales executive of a machine tool manufacturing company.

3
00:00:19,439 --> 00:00:24,849
He became excited about the problem and began to talk about his own experience with it.

4
00:00:25,520 --> 00:00:34,369
I've never heard it called that before," he said, but it is one of the most difficult problems every sales executive has to wrestle with.

5
00:00:34,560 --> 00:00:39,730
Just yesterday, a perfect example of what you're talking about happened in my company.

6
00:00:40,159 --> 00:00:47,010
One of the salesmen walked in about four o'clock with a $112,000 order for machine tools.

7
00:00:47,199 --> 00:00:52,770
Another salesman, whose volume is so low he's a problem, was in the office at the time.

8
00:00:52,960 --> 00:01:01,170
Hearing John tell the good news, he rather enviously congratulated him and then said, Well, John, you're lucky again.

9
00:01:01,679 --> 00:01:07,570
Now, what the weak salesman won't accept is that luck had nothing to do with John's big order.

10
00:01:07,759 --> 00:01:10,530
John had been working on that customer for months.

11
00:01:10,799 --> 00:01:14,369
He had talked repeatedly to a half dozen people out there.

12
00:01:14,719 --> 00:01:18,929
John had stayed up nights figuring out exactly what was best for them.

13
00:01:19,199 --> 00:01:23,570
Then he got our engineers to make preliminary designs of the equipment.

14
00:01:23,919 --> 00:01:30,929
John wasn't lucky, unless you can call carefully planned work and patiently executed plans luck.

15
00:01:32,079 --> 00:01:36,369
Suppose luck were used to reorganize General Motors.

16
00:01:36,639 --> 00:01:43,250
If luck determined who does what and who goes where, every business in the nation would fall apart.

17
00:01:43,599 --> 00:01:49,810
Assume for a moment that General Motors were to be completely reorganized on the basis of luck.

18
00:01:50,079 --> 00:01:55,889
To carry out the reorganization, the names of all employees would be placed in a barrel.

19
00:01:56,079 --> 00:02:01,329
The first name drawn would be the President, the second name the Executive Vice President,

20
00:02:01,359 --> 00:02:03,170
and so on down the line.

21
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:05,489
Sounds stupid, doesn't it?

22
00:02:05,599 --> 00:02:08,050
Well, that's how luck would work.

23
00:02:08,719 --> 00:02:14,610
People who rise to the top in any occupation, business management, selling, law,

24
00:02:14,639 --> 00:02:24,130
engineering, acting, or what have you, get there because they have superior attitudes and use their good sense in applied hard work.

